{
  "doc_id": "39245",
  "text": "In the process of APP hydrolysis into Aβ, APP intracellular C-terminal domain (AICD) will also be generated [CITATION_1] . With the transcription of histone acetylation-regulatory genes, AICD, Fe65, and Tip60 (HAT) can form into trimeric complexes. It has been demonstrated that AD-related genes including APP, GSK-3β, BACE1, and NEP are all regulated by the AICD-Fe65 complex [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The AICD-Fe65 complex is also involved in APP processing and management. The overexpression of Fe65 will generate more Aβ and promote the occurrence and development of AD [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
